{#- ---------- macros ---------- -#}
{%- from 'macros.j2' import fill as _fill -%}
{%- macro fill(value, width='180px') -%}
  {{- _fill(value, width, 5) -}}
{%- endmacro -%}

{%- macro box(checked) -%}
  {#- tolerate undefined/missing keys: a missing checkbox is simply unchecked -#}
  <span class="cb">{{ '☒' if (checked is defined and checked) else '☐' }}</span>
{%- endmacro -%}

{%- set L = lease | default({}) -%}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<style>
  @page {
    size: Letter;
    margin: 54px 56px 64px 56px;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  body {
    font-family: "Times New Roman", Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 9.2pt;
    line-height: 1.34;
    color: #111;
  }

  /* ---------- header / logo ---------- */
  .masthead { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; padding-bottom: 6px; }
  .logo {
    width: 46px; height: 46px; flex: 0 0 46px;
    border: 2px solid #1a3a5c; border-radius: 6px;
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    color: #1a3a5c; font-weight: bold; font-size: 17pt;
    font-family: Georgia, serif; letter-spacing: -1px;
  }
  .masthead .org { font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 8pt; letter-spacing: 2px; color:#1a3a5c; line-height:1.25; }
  .masthead .title-block { margin-left: auto; text-align: right; }
  .doc-title { font-weight: bold; font-size: 12.5pt; letter-spacing: .5px; }
  .doc-sub   { font-size: 8pt; color:#333; }
  .rule { border: none; border-top: 2px solid #1a3a5c; margin: 4px 0 10px 0; }
  .rule-thin { border:none; border-top:1px solid #999; margin: 9px 0; }

  /* ---------- preamble ---------- */
  .preamble { margin-bottom: 8px; }

  /* ---------- clauses ---------- */
  .clause { margin: 0 0 7px 0; text-align: justify; }
  .clause > .num { font-weight: bold; }
  .clause-title { font-weight: bold; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing:.3px; }
  .sub  { margin: 2px 0 2px 20px; text-align: justify; }
  .subsub { margin: 2px 0 2px 40px; text-align: justify; }
  .sublabel { font-weight: bold; }

  /* ---------- fill-in fields & checkboxes ---------- */
  .field {
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 4px;
    line-height: 1.05;
  }
  .field.filled {
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: bold;
    color: #13335c;
    text-decoration-color: #000;
  }
  .cb { font-size: 11pt; vertical-align: -1px; padding-right: 2px; }

  /* ---------- initials line ---------- */
  .initials {
    margin-top: 10px; padding-top: 4px; border-top: 1px solid #bbb;
    font-size: 8pt; color:#333; display:flex; justify-content: space-between;
  }

  /* ---------- table (move-in style) ---------- */
  table.grid { width:100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 4px 0 6px 0; font-size: 8.4pt; }
  table.grid th, table.grid td { border: 1px solid #444; padding: 3px 5px; text-align:left; }
  table.grid th { background:#eef2f6; font-weight:bold; }

  .section-banner {
    margin-top: 4px; padding: 5px 8px; background:#1a3a5c; color:#fff;
    font-weight:bold; font-size: 10pt; letter-spacing:.5px;
  }
  .page-break { break-before: page; }
  .small { font-size: 7.6pt; color:#444; }
  .notice-box { border:1px solid #444; padding:6px 8px; margin:6px 0; background:#fbfbf5; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

{#- ============================ PAGE 1 ============================ -#}
<div class="masthead">
  <div class="logo">M</div>
  <div class="org">MERIDIAN<br>PROPERTY<br>FORMS</div>
  <div class="title-block">
    <div class="doc-title">RESIDENTIAL LEASE AGREEMENT</div>
    <div class="doc-sub">Fixed-Term or Month-to-Month &middot; Form MRL-204 (Rev. 03/24)</div>
  </div>
</div>
<hr class="rule">

<div class="preamble">
This Residential Lease Agreement (this &ldquo;Agreement&rdquo;) is made on
{{ fill(L.date_made, '140px') }} between {{ fill(L.landlord_name, '210px') }}
(&ldquo;Landlord&rdquo;) and {{ fill(L.tenant_name, '210px') }} (&ldquo;Tenant&rdquo;),
who agree as follows.
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">1.</span> <span class="clause-title">Premises.</span>
  Landlord leases to Tenant the residential premises located at
  {{ fill(L.property_address, '300px') }} (the &ldquo;Premises&rdquo;), together with
  the fixtures and personal property described in Section&nbsp;4. The Premises shall be
  occupied solely as a private residence by the following named occupants and no others:
  {{ fill(L.occupants, '320px') }}.
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">2.</span> <span class="clause-title">Term.</span>
  <span class="sublabel">(Check A or B):</span>
  <div class="sub">
    {{ box(L.term_is_month_to_month) }} <span class="sublabel">A. Month-to-Month.</span>
    This Agreement begins on {{ fill(L.start_date, '120px') }} and continues as a
    month-to-month tenancy until terminated by either party on at least thirty (30) days&rsquo;
    written notice given in the manner required by law.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    {{ box(L.term_is_fixed) }} <span class="sublabel">B. Fixed Term.</span>
    This Agreement begins on {{ fill(L.start_date, '120px') }} and ends at 11:59&nbsp;PM on
    {{ fill(L.end_date, '120px') }}, unless (i)&nbsp;extended in a writing signed by both
    parties; (ii)&nbsp;terminated earlier under Section&nbsp;14; or (iii)&nbsp;Landlord accepts
    Rent after the end date, in which case a month-to-month tenancy is created under
    paragraph&nbsp;2A above.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">3.</span> <span class="clause-title">Rent.</span>
  Tenant shall pay Rent of {{ fill(L.rent_amount, '110px') }} per month, in advance, due on the
  {{ fill(L.rent_due_day, '40px') }} day of each calendar month and delinquent thereafter.
  &ldquo;Rent&rdquo; means all monetary obligations of Tenant under this Agreement except the
  security deposit described in Section&nbsp;5.
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">A.</span> Rent is payable by {{ box(L.pay_check) }} personal check
    {{ box(L.pay_transfer) }} electronic transfer {{ box(L.pay_other) }} other:
    {{ fill(L.pay_other_desc, '150px') }}, payable to {{ fill(L.payee, '180px') }}.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">B.</span> If any payment is returned unpaid, Tenant shall pay a
    returned-payment fee of {{ fill(L.nsf_fee, '70px') }} and, after the second such event,
    Landlord may require all future Rent to be paid by certified funds.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">4.</span> <span class="clause-title">Included Personal Property.</span>
  The following items are provided with the Premises and are to be returned in the same
  condition, ordinary wear and tear excepted: {{ fill(L.included_property, '330px') }}
  {{ box(L.property_addendum_attached) }} (if checked) additional items are listed on the
  attached inventory addendum.
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">5.</span> <span class="clause-title">Security Deposit.</span>
  Tenant shall deposit {{ fill(L.deposit_amount, '110px') }} as security for Tenant&rsquo;s
  performance. Landlord may apply the deposit, as reasonably necessary, to: (i)&nbsp;unpaid
  Rent; (ii)&nbsp;repair of damage beyond ordinary wear and tear caused by Tenant or
  Tenant&rsquo;s guests; (iii)&nbsp;cleaning of the Premises upon termination; and
  (iv)&nbsp;the replacement of personal property described in Section&nbsp;4. The deposit
  shall not be applied by Tenant to the last month&rsquo;s Rent. Within the period required by
  applicable law after Tenant vacates, Landlord shall return the balance of the deposit together
  with an itemized statement of any amounts withheld.
</div>

<div class="initials">
  <span>Tenant&rsquo;s Initials: ( {{ L.tenant_initials | default('______') }} )</span>
  <span>Landlord&rsquo;s Initials: ( {{ L.landlord_initials | default('______') }} )</span>
</div>

{#- ============================ PAGE 2 ============================ -#}
<div class="page-break"></div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">6.</span> <span class="clause-title">Maintenance, Use, and Reporting.</span>
  This is intentionally one of the long clauses in this Agreement and is meant to exceed the
  several-hundred-token range so that retrieval and chunking behaviour can be tested on a single
  dense block of obligations.
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">A.</span> Tenant shall properly use, operate, and safeguard the
    Premises, including any landscaping, furniture, furnishings, appliances, and all mechanical,
    electrical, gas, and plumbing fixtures, and shall keep them and the Premises clean, sanitary,
    and well ventilated. Tenant shall be responsible for checking and maintaining all smoke and
    carbon-monoxide detectors and shall replace batteries and burned-out bulbs as needed.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">B.</span> Tenant shall promptly notify Landlord in writing of any
    problem, malfunction, or damage. Tenant shall be charged for all repairs or replacements
    caused by Tenant, Tenant&rsquo;s pets, guests, or licensees, excluding ordinary wear and tear,
    and shall be charged for damage resulting from Tenant&rsquo;s failure to give timely notice.
    Tenant shall be charged for the repair of drain blockages or stoppages, unless caused by
    defective plumbing or by tree roots invading sewer lines.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">C.</span> Responsibility for the garden, landscaping, trees, and shrubs
    is allocated as follows: watering shall be performed by {{ box(L.water_landlord) }} Landlord
    {{ box(L.water_tenant) }} Tenant; routine maintenance shall be performed by
    {{ box(L.maint_landlord) }} Landlord {{ box(L.maint_tenant) }} Tenant; except as follows:
    {{ fill(L.landscaping_except, '230px') }}.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">D.</span> The parties agree that state or local water-use restrictions
    supersede any watering or maintenance obligation under paragraphs&nbsp;6C above. Tenant&rsquo;s
    failure to maintain any item for which Tenant is responsible entitles Landlord to perform such
    maintenance and charge Tenant the reasonable cost, which shall be deemed additional Rent under
    Section&nbsp;3.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">E.</span> Tenant shall not, without Landlord&rsquo;s prior written
    consent: (i)&nbsp;make alterations, repairs, or improvements, including painting, wallpapering,
    or changing locks; (ii)&nbsp;install antennas, satellite dishes, or signs; or
    (iii)&nbsp;deduct from Rent the cost of any repair, alteration, or improvement. Any such
    deduction shall be treated as unpaid Rent.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">7.</span> <span class="clause-title">Pets.</span>
  No animal shall be kept on or about the Premises without Landlord&rsquo;s prior written consent,
  except as expressly permitted in the attached Pet Addendum (see Schedule&nbsp;A). A service
  animal or assistance animal required by law is not a pet for purposes of this Section.
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">8.</span> <span class="clause-title">Quiet Enjoyment; Nuisance.</span>
  Tenant shall not disturb, annoy, endanger, or interfere with other residents or neighbours, nor
  use the Premises for any unlawful purpose, nor commit waste or nuisance on or about the Premises.
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">9.</span> <span class="clause-title">Entry.</span>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">A.</span> Tenant shall make the Premises available to Landlord or
    Landlord&rsquo;s agents to make necessary or agreed repairs, to supply agreed services, or to
    show the Premises to prospective tenants, purchasers, lenders, or contractors.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">B.</span> Except in the cases listed in paragraph&nbsp;9C, Landlord
    shall give Tenant at least twenty-four (24) hours&rsquo; written notice before entry. No notice
    is required: (i)&nbsp;in an emergency; (ii)&nbsp;if Tenant is present and consents at the time of
    entry; or (iii)&nbsp;if Tenant has abandoned or surrendered the Premises.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">C.</span> {{ box(L.keysafe_authorized) }} (If checked) Tenant authorizes
    the use of a keysafe/lockbox to permit entry under the conditions stated in paragraph&nbsp;9A.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">10.</span> <span class="clause-title">Assignment and Subletting.</span>
  Tenant shall not sublet the Premises or assign this Agreement without Landlord&rsquo;s prior
  written consent. This prohibition {{ box(L.sublet_short_term_applies) }} applies
  {{ box(L.sublet_short_term_excluded) }} does not apply to short-term, vacation, or transient
  rentals arranged through any hosting platform. Any violation of this Section is a non-curable,
  material breach of this Agreement.
</div>

<div class="initials">
  <span>Tenant&rsquo;s Initials: ( {{ L.tenant_initials | default('______') }} )</span>
  <span>Landlord&rsquo;s Initials: ( {{ L.landlord_initials | default('______') }} )</span>
</div>

{#- ============================ PAGE 3 ============================ -#}
<div class="page-break"></div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">11.</span> <span class="clause-title">Statutory and Condition Disclosures.</span>
  The following disclosures form part of this Agreement and are made by Landlord to Tenant as of
  the start date. Each lettered item applies only if the associated box is checked; an unchecked
  box means the disclosure does not apply to this tenancy and that Tenant should not infer any
  representation from its absence. This Section is intentionally written at length, with several
  conditional and nested provisions, so that retrieval, citation, and refusal behaviour can be
  exercised against a dense disclosure block of the kind commonly found at the back of a lease.
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">A.</span> {{ box(L.disc_lead_paint) }} <span class="sublabel">Pre-1978
    Construction.</span> If checked, the Premises were built before 1978, and Tenant acknowledges
    receipt of (i)&nbsp;the lead-based-paint disclosure referenced in Schedule&nbsp;A;
    (ii)&nbsp;the federally approved pamphlet on lead-poisoning prevention; and (iii)&nbsp;any
    records in Landlord&rsquo;s possession concerning lead-based paint in the Premises. If the box
    is not checked, Landlord makes no representation under this paragraph.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">B.</span> {{ box(L.disc_pest) }} <span class="sublabel">Periodic Pest
    Control.</span> If checked, Landlord has contracted for periodic pest-control treatment and
    shall provide Tenant a copy of any notice received from the pest-control operator. Tenant shall:
    (a)&nbsp;cooperate with reasonable access for treatment; and (b)&nbsp;follow any written
    preparation instructions provided in advance of a scheduled treatment.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">C.</span> {{ box(L.disc_flood) }} <span class="sublabel">Flood
    Hazard.</span> If checked, the Premises are located in a designated flood-hazard area. Tenant is
    advised that (i)&nbsp;Landlord&rsquo;s insurance does not cover Tenant&rsquo;s personal property;
    and (ii)&nbsp;flood insurance for Tenant&rsquo;s belongings, if desired, is the sole
    responsibility of Tenant.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">D.</span> {{ box(L.disc_mold) }} <span class="sublabel">Mold and
    Ventilation.</span> If checked, the Premises were previously treated for elevated levels of mold.
    In all cases, whether or not this box is checked, Tenant agrees to: (a)&nbsp;keep the Premises
    properly ventilated; (b)&nbsp;promptly report any water intrusion, leak, or visible mold growth;
    and (c)&nbsp;refrain from blocking vents or exhaust fans. Tenant&rsquo;s failure to comply may be
    treated as a failure to maintain under Section&nbsp;6.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">E.</span> <span class="sublabel">Registered-Offender Database.</span>
    Information about registered offenders is made available to the public on a database maintained
    by the responsible state agency. Neither Landlord nor any agent is required to check the
    database on Tenant&rsquo;s behalf, and Tenant may consult the database directly if Tenant wishes
    to obtain such information.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">12.</span> <span class="clause-title">Insurance.</span>
  Tenant&rsquo;s personal property is not insured by Landlord. Tenant is advised to carry
  renter&rsquo;s insurance. {{ box(L.insurance_required) }} (If checked) Tenant shall obtain and
  maintain liability insurance of not less than {{ fill(L.insurance_amount, '110px') }}, naming
  Landlord as an additional insured, and shall provide proof of coverage before the start date.
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">13.</span> <span class="clause-title">Move-In Condition.</span>
  The condition of the Premises at move-in is recorded below. Items not listed are presumed clean
  and in operable condition.
  <table class="grid">
    <thead>
      <tr><th style="width:34%">Area / Item</th><th style="width:14%">Condition</th><th style="width:52%">Comments</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for row in L.condition_rows | default([]) %}
      <tr><td>{{ row.area }}</td><td>{{ row.condition }}</td><td>{{ row.comments }}</td></tr>
      {% else %}
      <tr><td>Living area</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Kitchen / appliances</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Bathroom(s)</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Flooring / walls</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">14.</span> <span class="clause-title">Early Termination.</span>
  If Tenant terminates before the end of the term stated in Section&nbsp;2B, Tenant remains
  responsible for lost Rent, reasonable re-rental costs, and advertising expenses, which Landlord
  may withhold from the security deposit described in Section&nbsp;5.
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">15.</span> <span class="clause-title">Waiver.</span>
  Landlord&rsquo;s waiver of any breach shall not be a waiver of any later breach.
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">16.</span> <span class="clause-title">Entire Agreement.</span>
  This Agreement, together with any addendum or schedule incorporated by reference, is the final
  and complete expression of the parties&rsquo; agreement and supersedes all prior or contemporaneous
  oral agreements. Any modification must be in a writing signed by both parties.
</div>

<div class="initials">
  <span>Tenant&rsquo;s Initials: ( {{ L.tenant_initials | default('______') }} )</span>
  <span>Landlord&rsquo;s Initials: ( {{ L.landlord_initials | default('______') }} )</span>
</div>

{#- ============================ PAGE 4 — ADDENDUM (numbering resets) ============================ -#}
<div class="page-break"></div>

<div class="masthead">
  <div class="logo">M</div>
  <div class="org">MERIDIAN<br>PROPERTY<br>FORMS</div>
  <div class="title-block">
    <div class="doc-title">SCHEDULE A &mdash; PET ADDENDUM</div>
    <div class="doc-sub">Attached to and part of Form MRL-204 &middot; Form MRL-PET (Rev. 03/24)</div>
  </div>
</div>
<hr class="rule">

<div class="preamble">
This Pet Addendum is incorporated into and made part of the Residential Lease Agreement dated
{{ fill(L.date_made, '140px') }} for the Premises at {{ fill(L.property_address, '280px') }}.
Where this Addendum conflicts with the main Agreement, this Addendum controls as to pets.
Notwithstanding Section&nbsp;7 of the Agreement, Landlord grants permission for Tenant to keep the
following pet(s) only: {{ fill(L.pets_permitted, '300px') }}.
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">1.</span> <span class="clause-title">Permitted Pets Only.</span>
  Tenant shall keep no animal other than those identified above, including animals that are
  &ldquo;just visiting,&rdquo; without Landlord&rsquo;s further written consent.
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">2.</span> <span class="clause-title">Pet Deposit and Rent.</span>
  Tenant shall pay an additional pet deposit of {{ fill(L.pet_deposit, '100px') }} and additional
  monthly pet rent of {{ fill(L.pet_rent, '100px') }}, which is part of &ldquo;Rent&rdquo; under
  Section&nbsp;3 of the Agreement.
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">3.</span> <span class="clause-title">Tenant Obligations.</span>
  Tenant agrees that the pet(s) will be: (i)&nbsp;properly licensed and vaccinated as required by
  law; (ii)&nbsp;kept under control and not left unattended in common areas; and
  (iii)&nbsp;prevented from causing damage, odour, or disturbance. Tenant shall promptly remove and
  dispose of all pet waste.
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">4.</span> <span class="clause-title">Liability.</span>
  Tenant is responsible for, and shall indemnify Landlord against, all damage and all claims for
  injury arising from the pet(s), whether or not the specific animal is listed above.
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">5.</span> <span class="clause-title">Revocation.</span>
  Landlord may revoke permission to keep a pet on {{ fill(L.pet_revoke_days, '50px') }} days&rsquo;
  written notice for cause. Tenant&rsquo;s failure to remove the pet after revocation is a breach of
  the Agreement.
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="num">6.</span>
  {{ box(L.pet_insurance_required) }} <span class="clause-title">Renter&rsquo;s Insurance for Pets
  (if checked).</span> Tenant shall carry renter&rsquo;s insurance that includes coverage for pet
  ownership and shall provide proof on request.
</div>

<div class="notice-box small">
  By signing below, Tenant acknowledges having read, understood, and received a copy of this
  Pet Addendum.
</div>

<table class="grid" style="margin-top:14px;">
  <tr>
    <td style="width:50%">Tenant: {{ fill(L.tenant_name, '160px') }}</td>
    <td style="width:25%">Date: {{ fill(L.sign_date, '90px') }}</td>
    <td style="width:25%">Sign: ____________</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Landlord: {{ fill(L.landlord_name, '160px') }}</td>
    <td>Date: {{ fill(L.sign_date, '90px') }}</td>
    <td>Sign: ____________</td>
  </tr>
</table>

</body>
</html>
